description.0: Sheila Van Reynolds was the center of attention with her money, smarts and beauty. But does the spotlight blind Sheila from love?
description.4: The Creature of the Black Bog emerges...
description.5: An ignorant man foolishly agrees to release an evil extraterrestrial from his TV set...but nothing goes to plan!
description.6: Jack Kirby set the standard for massive monster mayhem covers before the super hero boom. So bringing those elements together? Magical.
description.9: Meet a creature who can stomp on our planet with a single step!
description.10: We all know how impactful The Rawhide Kid's identity is, but what happens when someone kidnaps him and attempts to steal it by matching his appearance?
description.11: Monsteroso invades Earth and needs to be stopped; the only problem is that bullets bounce right off of him!
description.14: Behold Bruttu! Bruttu, formerly a scrawny guy, becomes an amalgamation of monsters as a result of his imagination being converted to matter.
description.15: Whatever you do...don't wake the Abominable Snowman! A camera crew gets more than they bargained for when they encounter the actual monstrosity of their script's premise.
description.21: Klagg wages war onto Earth! But the reason behind this affront may have just cause...
description.22: An occult African woodcarving comes to life. Thus the origin of... Moomba!
description.23: Scientist Jonathan Wilkes creates a powerful robot that goes on to build his own army...
description.24: The Kid's origins retold, rendered by the legendary Jack Kirby! This issue brings The Kid's story to life more than ever before. Additionally, we see The Kid wonder if his violent lifestyle will ever end, and if he can ever find peace.
description.25: A young man and his girlfriend are trapped in the Age of Dinosaurs!
description.28: A Hollywood stunt is pulled off to confuse and destroy the Colossus!
description.29: A high-school student accidentally unleashes the 'Crawling Creature' during a mining experiment. Now the monster is the enemy at hand!
description.32: Botany can be considered an art form. If so, a man has created quite a dangerous masterpiece.
description.33: An extraterrestrial supplants its consciousness into a steam shovel and takes to rampage! And things only get weirder from there!
description.34: A high school student helps chase down a criminal named Manoo!
description.35: The Rawhide Kid, relatively unscathed by human opponents, may have finally met his match...the "Living Totem"! This larger than life, durable creature has only one goal in mind -- to get revenge by wiping out the entire human race.
description.36: A mysterious alien warrior lands on Earth!
description.39: Kraa the Unhuman is born, and must decide if he hates humanity or if it is worth saving.
description.40: Anything a writer puts down on paper comes to life! Sometimes your most beautiful creations can try and kill you.
description.43: Little did we know the mighty Goom has left a son on Earth! His name is Googam and he can really throw a tantrum!
description.44: A convicted felon has a choice: let Rommbu wreak havoc or save the world by sacrificing himself...
description.46: The infamous Rawhide Kid is finally recognized and captured, this time by a real U.S. Marshall, The Kid's ultimate fear. Can he manage to find a way out of this one, and escape the hands of the law?
description.49: An escaped criminal volunteers to take part of an experiment. One that will put him in a suit of indestructible armor so the cops can never catch him!
description.50: The return of Gorgilla! But this time will he behave like a man...or like a beast?
description.53: Behold Goom! The Thing from Planet X!
description.54: A creation in a wax museum is struck by lightning. You can guess what happens next!
description.56: How far will The Kid go in an attempt to become a free man once again? Will he give in when a convincing, yet fake U.S. Marshall asks him to relinquish his weapons?
description.59: Boris Petrovsky has accidentally created the Colossus!
description.60: An archeologist wakes up a once-dormant rock monster...and this creature's none too pleased to have its nap interrupted!
description.63: A giant robot built to be smarter than human beings craves world domination.
description.64: The Blip, an alien made of living electricity has come to Earth!
description.65: Nearly a dozen stories featuring everyone's favorite model MILLIE! Millie still hasn't found the underlying cause of why Chili hates her!
description.67: What happens when The Kid is recognized in public by a potential challenger? On the other end of the spectrum, what happens when The Kid falls in love, but faces the conundrum of being recognized as the infamous outlaw he actually is?
description.70: Krang now has the ability to have complex thought, and with that comes a scheme for world domination!
description.73: Gor-Kill, a gaseous demon, merges with the water in order to manifest into an immensely powerful form!
description.74: The First Appearance of Groot!  Before becoming a Guardian of the Galaxy, Groot was a terrifying monster from Planet X.  Possessing a vocabulary larger than "I am Groot", Groot's Marvel Monster origins are revealed here!
description.76: Wolf Waco tests the Rawhide Kid's toughness, questioning if his words really translate into his actions. In this issue, witness some good ol' fashioned fistfights, epic train robberies, and The Kid's major moral conflict.
description.79: Half-man, half-ape - 100% beast. On an expedition to uncover the missing link of man, a team of scientists finds an unusual case study in Gorgilla.
description.81: What to do when you don't have a date for the dance!
description.82: A mad scientist tries to play Dr. Frankenstein with a result that may be even worse than the Mary Shelley novel.
description.83: Those who meet Monstrom wish he'd crawl back to the swamp that birthed him. He's a one-eyed mindless destroyer.
description.85: From the incomparable Stan Lee comes Rawhide Kid! This hidden gem brings the word "Western" to a whole new level. We find out if the "Rawhide Kid" himself is truly a cold-blooded killer, and his early origins before he became the lovable outlaw we know and love.
description.88: In this near-Homeric epic, a mighty Cyclops is awoken from his long slumber and begins a destructive rampage!
description.89: Welcome Titano, the monster that time mistakenly forgot!
description.93: While chasing an adventure, a few unlucky men encounter a demon from the Fifth Dimension! And, the first appearance of Chondu the Mystic!
description.94: Even modern missiles can't damage this massive behemoth taking to the streeets!
description.98: Off the coast of Russia, an enormous octo-fiend emerges from the murk! Meet Monstro!
description.99: A magnificent mummy is reborn to launch an attack against the world!

1.text: Kid Colt invades the wrong “Outlaw Town” where he faces the justice of Judge Jesse James!

2.text: A stranded man encounters a legendary being who convinces him to release a pack of demons from a box.

3.text: Meet Orrgo, a being from another planet with the ability to hypnotize and control the human population!

6.text: The Fantastic Four spring to action as a team for the first time. As they learn how to control their new found powers, will it be enough to stop the fury of the Mole Man?

7.text: Gunslinging tales from the Old West brought to you by some of Marvel’s classic creators! Featuring Kid Colt and Montana Brown.

8.text: Steve Stuart fears he’ll lose Linda Carter’s love to one of her lovestruck patients!

12.text: An atomic research scientist heads into the lab with an arachnid threat in tow.

13.text: Marvel Master Jack Kirby introduces Fin Fang Foom!

16.text: Kathy Carter may face competition over attention from a boy!

17.text: Patsy Walker... a bride? Find out who’s the lucky groom in this monumental issue!

18.text: Millie turns a fashion faux pas into a fashion moment! Co-starring Chili Storm.

71.text: Escaped inmate Joe Harper has created a monster…Xemnu the Living Hulk.
